{"tags":["open"],"date":"2009-11-19T15:21:25Z","author":"Simon Chiang <simon.chiang@pinnacol.com>","type":"issue","content":"Storage could look like this:\r\n\r\n  /gitgo\r\n    /users\r\n      /email # (doc)\r\n\r\nThen the document:\r\n\r\n  [email]\r\n  ---\r\n  author: name <email>\r\n  date: date added or updated\r\n  password: sha\r\n  ---\r\n  bio\r\n\r\nThe password is the sha1 digest of 'passwordsecret'.  That way all users running on a server with a given secret will be enabled.  If you don't know the secret, all users using that secret will be locked out.\r\n\r\nThis also implies that authentication middleware is only added when gitgo is running with a secret.","at":"e7652914295bbfc2b6a72882d30e04519a2ecc2f","state":"open"}